==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monoecious
<hw>Mo*noe"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Having the sexes united in one individual, as when male and female
flowers grow upon the same individual plant; hermaphrodite; -- opposed
to <ant>dioecious</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monoecism</ent>⟦br⟧
